Well, so that's how I flew today.
First criticism point: We need more attractive logbooks. Black is boring, pink is not really pink, but salmon-colored.
I wanted to fly since I was a child.
And today it was finally... I flew an airplane today. I haven't quite processed it yet.
Data from FlightAware.
I'm trying to drive down again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's still Monday.
It is already becoming clear where the problems lie. It is probably going to BE VERY difficult to obtain medical clearance, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It is not impossible, but it will TAKE A VERY LONG TIME and means A LOT OF extra work.
That is somewhat discouraging, but it's still just another problem that one has to solve. So far, it seems solvable. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what awaits me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you medical clearance if you're taking medication for it.
